# .banned-patterns.local — personal names and terms to block from committing.
# Copy this file to .banned-patterns.local (gitignored) and add your own terms.
# One pattern per line. Lines starting with # are comments. Case-sensitive.
#
# The pre-commit hook scans staged files against this list.
# GitHub Actions CI does NOT have access to this file (it's gitignored) —
# it only enforces structural rules (hardcoded paths, emails).
# This file is your LOCAL safety net for personal names.
#
# Example entries (remove these and add your own):
# firstname
# surname
# nickname
# case-keyword
